Choose one of three fission track dating methods:
<ol><li>'EDM' = the External Detector Method: determines the sample's uranium content by proxy, using neutron-induced tracks recorded in a mica detector; 
</li><li>'ICP (&zeta;)': determines the uranium content directly by LA-ICP-MS using a zeta calibration 
approach in which all measurements are normalised to age standards;
</li><li>'ICP (absolute)': uses LA-ICP-MS without age standards, assuming that the fission decay constant, etch efficiency factor and uranium concentrations are known with sufficient accuracy.
</li></ol>
